EPISODE #3 \"The Insatiable Appetite of Drone Raper\"', '
<h2 class=\"firstheader\">synopsis:</h2>
<p>You don\'t have to be a Mad Men fanatic to savor The Mad World of Miss Hathaway, a musical take-off on the ultra-popular TV show set in the early 1960\'s.  After remounting episodes #1 \"The Torment of Penny Trollson\" &amp; #2 \"Who\'s Eating Lance Borgotto?\" at the East Village performance space, The Wild Project, Angela Di Carlo is unveiling a  new episode focused around the most popular ad man in town, the insatiable Drone Raper.</p>
<p>Di Carlo imagines newfangled plots and spirited Mad songs as she portrays JoAnne Hathaway, the know-it-all red-headed secretary of Spencer-Colfax advertising agency.  She\'s joined by a hilarious supporting cast—Adam Dugas (Dueling Harps, Chaos &amp; Candy) James Kaliardos and Patrick Johnson with musical accompaniment by Todd Almond. It\'s a spirited pop-culture tribute not to be missed!</p>', 'THE_MAD_WORLD_OF_MISS_HATHAWAYEPISODE_3_The_Insatiable_Appetite_of_Drone_Raper', '2018-05-06 15:06:29', '2018-05-06 15:06:29', '2018-05-06 15:06:29', '2018-05-06 15:06:29', 1, 'publish','performancearchive'); 
